text.section:
Administrative regulations promulgated by the board under subsection (3) of this section shall specify:
The regulatory areas which may be exempted or modified if approved by the state board, except as provided in KRS 160.107(2) and in addition to those areas identified in KRS 160.107(3);
The application, plan review, approval, and amendment process for a district;
Timelines for initial approval as a district of innovation, the renewal process, and on-going evaluative procedures required of the district;
Acceptable documentation of a critical mass of parental, community, educator, and business support and capacity to effect a change;
The approvals required of the plan by certain employees of a school;
Evidence of teacher collaboration and shared leadership within the district and the schools to be designated as schools of innovation;
The process of revocation of the designation of district of innovation or school of innovation;
Reporting and oversight responsibilities of the district and the Kentucky Department of Education;
The financial detail relating to budgets of schools and evidence of sound fiscal management practices;
Acceptable areas of emphasis for innovation;
Acceptable documentation of job-embedded professional development within the proposed innovation design; and
Other components deemed necessary to implement this section and KRS 160.107.
